\caption[]{Time evolution of the angle between a CH bond and an adjacent CC bond, from the moment the field is turned on and the molecule starts rotating about Ox. Note the change in character of the motion, from the response of the H atom alone to the initial electric kick, during the first picosecond, to the later, much faster oscillations including in-plane and out-of-plane CH bending modes.}
\label{Fig:startB}
